Hey! Great to have you back Robo. 

::Squizzy::
She checked on the Feline clone and it was now 100% completed. She 
opened the tank and slowly hauled the clone up onto the table. She 
sighed and repeated the proccess on this clone as she did for 
Beholder.  Only the mother boards weren't as intact as they were for 
Beholder, and the memory chips for Feline were most burned and 
charred to the point that they couldn't be used. She pulled out what 
she could from the remains and installed them into Feline2.  She took 
out the remains of hte origianl spark chamber. She had to fix it up 
and make some major repairs to it. She opened up the chest panel on 
the clone and installed the spark chamber. She filled it with energon 
and then closed it all up. She went over to the console and finished 
uploading all the memories she could salvage.  Then she sent the 
electricity through the body to start the spark generating.

She could only sit by and hope for the best on this one. She shook 
her head. "By the matrix I hope I never have this happens to me."
